The Special Adviser to the Edo State Governor on Media and Communication Strategy, Crusoe Osagie, has said Governor Godwin Obaseki’s convincing all-round performance in the past four years has earned him an organic following among Edo people and the electorate. Osagie, in a statement, said the governor’s excellent performance, which has endeared him to Edo people, is causing the opposition sleepless nights and leaving them to search for means to undo the overwhelming support by Edo people. He stressed that the governor and his team have no reason whatsoever to coerce people to support him because his works speak for themselves and the people, especially teachers in the state, who have been immensely impacted by the governor’s policies. According to him, “The governor does not need to coerce teachers to support him. That is preposterous. No such thing happened. Obaseki’s following is organic and real. There is no such thing as threats for anyone to support the governor. “The strongest supporters of the Governor are teachers, whose lives and careers have been transformed by the governor’s reforms. As against what obtained in the past when teachers were ridiculed, we have made them more marketable, improved their skills and introduced them to more exciting ways of teaching and learning.” 